{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775856216786,"sessionID":"ses_286ba319cffeYTa9meQOZzGA4C","part":{"id":"prt_d7946ab00001xqgEEkJ9thBNNU","messageID":"msg_d7946986b001JUuXIuw2iKdqSf","sessionID":"ses_286ba319cffeYTa9meQOZzGA4C","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_1d7d064c31de446881a0344b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-023: CLI invoke/status 命令 — Tasks\n\n**Module:** `cmd/cli` | **Language:** Python | **Size:** M\n**Base specs:** `cli-toolkit/spec.md`, `cli-toolkit/design.md`, `delta-spec.md`\n\n---\n\n## T-1: InvokeRuntime class skeleton + constructor\n\n- [ ] Create `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` with `InvokeRuntime` class\n- [ ] Implement `__init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\")` setting `self.verbose` and `self.provider`\n- [ ] Add `InvokeRuntime` export to `agentcube/runtime/__init__.py`\n- [ ] Write test: constructor sets `verbose` and `provider` correctly (default and explicit values)\n\n## T-2: InvokeRuntime._validate_invoke_prerequisites\n\n- [ ] Implement `_validate_invoke_prerequisites(workspace_path: Path) -> tuple[AgentMetadata, str, str]`\n- [ ] Load metadata via `MetadataService`; raise `ValueError` if `agent_id` or `agent_endpoint` is missing\n- [ ] Return `(metadata, agent_id, endpoint)` tuple\n- [ ] Write test: valid workspace with published metadata returns tuple\n- [ ] Write test: missing `agent_id` raises `ValueError`\n- [ ] Write test: missing `agent_endpoint` raises `ValueError`\n\n## T-3: InvokeRuntime._direct_http_invocation\n\n- [ ] Implement `_direct_http_invocation(endpoint: str, payload: Dict, headers: Dict[str, str], workspace_path: Path) -> Dict`\n- [ ] POST JSON to `{endpoint}` using `httpx` (sync client)\n- [ ] Parse JSON response; return parsed dict\n- [ ] On non-2xx status, raise exception with status code and response body\n- [ ] Write test: successful POST returns parsed JSON response\n- [ ] Write test: non-2xx response raises exception with status code\n- [ ] Write test: custom headers are included in request\n\n## T-4: InvokeRuntime._invoke_agent_via_agentcube\n\n- [ ] Implement `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube(agent_id, payload, headers, endpoint, workspace_path) -> Dict`\n- [ ] Load metadata; if `k8s_deployment.type == \"AgentRuntime\"`, rewrite endpoint to `{base}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n- [ ] If `metadata.session_id` exists, inject header `X-Agentcube-Session-Id`\n- [ ] POST JSON to rewritten endpoint; return parsed response\n- [ ] Write test: endpoint rewriting when `k8s_deployment.type == \"AgentRuntime\"`\n- [ ] Write test: session header injection when `session_id` present\n- [ ] Write test: no rewriting when deployment type is not `AgentRuntime`\n- [ ] Write test: no session header when `session_id` is absent\n\n## T-5: InvokeRuntime.invoke (orchestration)\n\n- [ ] Implement `invoke(workspace_path: Path, payload: Dict, headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None) -> Dict`\n- [ ] Call `_validate_invoke_prerequisites` → get metadata, agent_id, endpoint\n- [ ] If `self.provider == \"agentcube\"`, call `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube`\n- [ ] Otherwise, call `_direct_http_invocation`\n- [ ] Return the response\n- [ ] Write test: provider=\"agentcube\" routes to `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube`\n- [ ] Write test: provider=\"k8s\" routes to `_direct_http_invocation`\n\n## T-6: invoke CLI command entry point\n\n- [ ] Add `invoke()` command to `agentcube/cli/main.py`\n- [ ] Options: `workspace` (`-f`, default `\".\"`), `payload` (`--payload`, default `\"{}\"`), `header_list` (`--header`, repeatable `List[str]`), `provider` (`--provider`, default `\"agentcube\"`), `verbose` (`--verbose`, default `False`)\n- [ ] Parse `--payload` as JSON; on invalid JSON, print `Error: Invalid JSON payload: {detail}` in red, exit code `1`\n- [ ] Parse `--header` entries: split on first `:`, strip key/value; on missing `:`, print `Error: Invalid header format. Expected 'key:value'.` in red, exit code `1`\n- [ ] Merge multiple headers into single `Dict[str, str]`\n- [ ] Call `InvokeRuntime.invoke()` within error handler\n- [ ] On success, print response (Rich-formatted if JSON, raw text otherwise)\n- [ ] On error, use `_handle_error(e, \"invoking agent\", verbose)`\n- [ ] Write test: successful invoke prints response, exit 0\n- [ ] Write test: invalid JSON payload → error message, exit 1\n- [ ] Write test: invalid header format → error message, exit 1\n- [ ] Write test: multiple headers merged correctly\n- [ ] Write test: verbose error prints traceback, exit 1\n- [ ] Write test: quiet error prints message only, exit 1\n\n## T-7: StatusRuntime class skeleton + constructor\n\n- [ ] Create `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py` with `StatusRuntime` class\n- [ ] Implement `__init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\")` setting `self.verbose` and `self.provider`\n- [ ] Add `StatusRuntime` export to `agentcube/runtime/__init__.py`\n- [ ] Write test: constructor sets `verbose` and `provider` correctly\n\n## T-8: StatusRuntime._get_cr_k8s_status\n\n- [ ] Implement `_get_cr_k8s_status(metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Dict`\n- [ ] Use `AgentCubeProvider.get_agent_runtime(name)` to fetch CR\n- [ ] If CR exists and has `status` field → return `{\"status\": cr_status, \"endpoint\": cr_agentEndpoint, ...}`\n- [ ] If CR exists but no `status` field → return `{\"status\": \"created_no_status\"}`\n- [ ] If CR not found → return `{\"status\": \"not_found_in_k8s\"}`\n- [ ] Write test: CR exists with status → returns status + endpoint\n- [ ] Write test: CR exists without status → returns `created_no_status`\n- [ ] Write test: CR not found → returns `not_found_in_k8s`\n\n## T-9: StatusRuntime._get_k8s_status\n\n- [ ] Implement `_get_k8s_status(metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Dict`\n- [ ] Call `KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status(agent_name)` (see T-11)\n- [ ] Return the result dict\n- [ ] Write test: calls `KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status` and returns result\n\n## T-10: StatusRuntime.get_status (orchestration)\n\n- [ ] Implement `get_status(workspace_path: Path, provider: Optional[str] = None) -> Dict`\n- [ ] Load metadata from workspace via `MetadataService`\n- [ ] If no `agent_id` → return `{\"status\": \"not_published\"}`\n- [ ] If `provider == \"agentcube\"` (or default), call `_get_cr_k8s_status`\n- [ ] Otherwise, call `_get_k8s_status`\n- [ ] Return the status dict\n- [ ] Write test: no `agent_id` → returns `not_published`\n- [ ] Write test: provider=\"agentcube\" routes to `_get_cr_k8s_status`\n- [ ] Write test: provider=\"k8s\" routes to `_get_k8s_status`\n\n## T-11: KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status\n\n- [ ] Add `get_agent_status(agent_name: str) -> Dict` to `KubernetesProvider`\n- [ ] Query deployment status via `AppsV1Api.read_namespaced_deployment_status`\n- [ ] Query pod status via `CoreV1Api.list_namespaced_pod` with label selector\n- [ ] Return dict with deployment status, pod statuses, endpoint info\n- [ ] On 404, return `{\"status\": \"not_found\"}`\n- [ ] Write test: deployment found with ready pods → returns status\n- [ ] Write test: deployment not found → returns `not_found`\n\n## T-12: status CLI command entry point\n\n- [ ] Add `status()` command to `agentcube/cli/main.py`\n- [ ] Options: `workspace` (`-f`, default `\".\"`), `provider` (`--provider`, default `\"agentcube\"`), `verbose` (`--verbose`, default `False`)\n- [ ] Call `StatusRuntime.get_status()`\n- [ ] If status == `\"not_published\"` → print guidance to run `publish` first, exit code `1`\n- [ ] If status == `\"error\"` → print error details, exit code `1`\n- [ ] Otherwise, render Rich `Table` with columns: Field, Value (at minimum: Agent Name, Status, Endpoint, Version, Provider)\n- [ ] On exception, use `_handle_error(e, \"getting status\", verbose)`\n- [ ] Write test: not_published → guidance message, exit 1\n- [ ] Write test: error status → error details, exit 1\n- [ ] Write test: valid status → Rich Table rendered with required fields\n- [ ] Write test: verbose error prints traceback, exit 1\n\n## T-13: Provider validation (cross-cutting)\n\n- [ ] Add provider validation to both `invoke` and `status` commands: reject values other than `\"agentcube\"` / `\"k8s\"`\n- [ ] Write test: invalid provider → error message, exit 1\n\n## T-14: Integration tests\n\n- [ ] Write integration test: full invoke flow with mocked HTTP (mock `httpx.Client`)\n- [ ] Write integration test: full status flow with mocked K8s (mock `AgentCubeProvider` / `KubernetesProvider`)\n- [ ] Write integration test: invoke with session header end-to-end (mocked)\n\n## T-15: Lint, type-check, coverage gate\n\n- [ ] `ruff check agentcube/` — no violations\n- [ ] `mypy agentcube/` — no type errors\n- [ ] `pytest tests/ -v` — all pass\n- [ ] `pytest tests/ --cov=agentcube --cov-report=term-missing` — coverage ≥ 80%\n\n---\n\n## Dependency Graph\n\n```\nT-1  ──┬── T-2 ──┬── T-5 ── T-6\n       │          │\n       │          └── T-4 ──┘\n       │\n       └── T-3 ──┘\n\nT-7  ──┬── T-8 ──┬── T-10 ── T-12\n       │          │\n       └── T-9 ──┘  (T-9 depends on T-11)\n\nT-11 ── T-9\n\nT-13 ── (T-6, T-12)\n\nT-14 ── (T-6, T-12)\n\nT-15 ── (all above)\n```\n\n## Parallelizable Groups\n\n| Group | Tasks | Prerequisites |\n|-------|-------|---------------|\n| G1 | T-1, T-7 | None |\n| G2 | T-2, T-3, T-11 | T-1 |\n| G3 | T-4, T-8, T-9 | T-2, T-11 |\n| G4 | T-5, T-10 | T-2, T-3, T-4, T-8, T-9 |\n| G5 | T-6, T-12, T-13 | T-5, T-10 |\n| G6 | T-14 | T-6, T-12 |\n| G7 | T-15 | All above |\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/tasks.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py\">\nERROR [28:35] \"CustomObjectsApi\" is not a known attribute of \"None\"\nERROR [125:20] Type \"str | list[list[Unknown] | dict[Unk